<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,352,775]" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">
Diagnosis:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. B. Liu &amp; Y. C. Dai" authorityYear="2021" box="[284,518,352,378]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Meruliaceae" genus="Steccherinum" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="112" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fragile">
<emphasis box="[284,518,352,378]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">Steccherinum fragile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by an annual growth habit, resupinate basidiocarps with salmon to peach pores when fresh becoming cinnamon buff to pinkish buff upon drying, margin thin with distinct rhizomorphs, a monomitic hyphal system, generative hyphae thin- to distinctly thick-walled with simple septa, neither amyloid nor cyanophilous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,352,775]" box="[189,1067,496,523]" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">
Etymology:—‘ 
<emphasis box="[359,443,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">Fragile</emphasis>
’ (Lat.) refers to the species having fragile basidiocarps.
</paragraph>
