<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1856,2062]" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis box="[189,354,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">Hyphal system</emphasis>
:—Monomitic; generative hyphae thin- to distinctly thick-walled, simple septate; all hyphae IKI–, CB–, unchanged in KOH.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1856,2062]" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis box="[189,307,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">Subiculum</emphasis>
:—Generative hyphae hyaline to pale yellowish brown, thin- to thick-walled, frequently branched, interwoven, 2.5–6.5 μm in diam; irregular crystals rarely present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1856,2062]" lastBlockId="7.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="113" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis box="[189,254,2000,2026]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="112">Tubes</emphasis>
:—Generative hyphae hyaline to pale yellowish brown, thin- to thick-walled, occasionally branched, interwoven, 2–6 μm in diam; irregular crystals rarely present; cystidia and cystidioles absent; basidia clavate, hyaline, thin-walled, bearing four sterigmata and a simple basal septum, 13–14 × 4–4.5 μm; basidioles barrel-shaped, 7–9 × 3–4.5 μm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,365]" pageId="7" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis box="[189,347,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="113">Basidiospores</emphasis>
:—Ellipsoid, hyaline, thin-walled, smooth, occasionally with one or two guttules, IKI–, CB–, (2.6–)2.8–3.1 × (2–)2.1–2.2(–2.5) μm, L = 2.96 μm, W = 2.11 μm, Q = 1.24–1.47 (n = 60/2).
</paragraph>
